speech.p: Will my right hon. Friend have a word with our excellent Secretary of State for Education and identify the best schools in the couneb;normal;jtry that tackle homophobic bullying and sexual harassment together with the parents of their pupils, and roll out that best practice across the country?

I welcome today’s statement, particularly the talk about connectivity with HS2, which will of course be greater if we get an HS2 hub at Crewe. Will the Secretary of State confirm that, once there are two runways at Heathrow, the proportion of slots available to domestic traffic will remain at least the same as it is now?
